\fs24 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Science Pipelines\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\b0 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://ls.st/ug"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul LSST Science Pipelines}} will implement the core image processing and data analysis algorithms needed to process optical survey imaging data at low latency and unprecedented scale and accuracy. We are writing pipelines for single-epoch image processing, coaddition, image differencing, optimal multi-epoch measurements, and (global) photometric and astrometric calibration, among others. \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319

\b \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Scalable Database\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\b0 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
To satisfy the need to efficiently store, query, and analyze catalogs running into trillions of row gs and petabytes of data, we are developing {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://ls.st/kth"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul Qserv}}, a distributed shared-nothing SQL database query system. \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319

\b \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
User Interface\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\b0 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
One of the most important jobs of a large survey is to provide access. This includes access to catalogs, processed images, and raw images. Access in the next generation of surveys will extend to visualization and analysis. We are writing interfaces that will allow thousands of users to query, download, visualize, and analyze petabytes of LSST data. \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319

\b \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Data Access Middleware\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\b0 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
In order to build a scalable, portable processing system, we are creating extensible middleware to transparently access data irrespective of storage location or format. \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319

\b \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Distributed Execution\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240

\b0 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The LSST data processing pipelines will need to efficiently scale from single core execution to tens of thousands of cores. To meet this requirement we are building an orchestration framework to launch and monitor jobs on many different systems at many different scales. \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298

